title: Shamrock and thistle;
author: Optic, Oliver
snippet: AFTER study hours the next day, the entire ship's company took the train at Kingstown for Dublin. Leaving the station in Great Brunswick Street in side cars, four and twenty of which were readily procured, the party proceeded to Dublin Castle. In passing through College Street, the procession of cars encountered the carriage of the lord mayor of the city, which produced a sensation among the republican  young gentlemen.
